From Sola Ojo, Kaduna The aspiration of the presidential candidate of the Labour Party, Peter Obi, got a boost in Kaduna, yesterday, as northern youths embarked on a solidarity walk in his favour. The youths, who represent different organisations called on the presidential hopeful to remain resolute in his campaign towards birthing a new  Nigeria where the security of lives and property could be guaranteed as against what was currently experiencing. Answering questions from newsmen at the sideline of the solidarity walk at the popular Tafawa Balewa Road, Kaduna, the convener who doubles as spokesperson of the Northern Youths Peter Obi Support Organisation, Victor Ododo said Nigerian youths were looking forward to a Peter Obi presidency to replicate what he did as Anambra State Governor between 2006-2014 across the country. “We are conversant with what our incoming President, Peter Obi has been doing over time. We have been here since yesterday, and today we are walking the street to inform fellow youths in Kaduna and by extension, across the North that we are with him,” said Ododo.